      <text>It's become slight common practice among some of us to use the sponsorship
rights that you guys have to get people into the guild as quickly as
possible, more often than not without roleplay.  The reason that we have a
seeking process is to discover who really wants to be in the guild and who
needs a bit more work before they join our lovely group.  The point of
this is to stress the importance of talking to seekers, roleplaying, and
being selective on who you sponsor.  If there are doubts in your mind as
to if the person you just roleplayed with has sufficient language skills
and creativity enough to fill the roll that they are looking to be in the
guild...  Take a little more time, talk to them, ask them to roleplay
again.  Don't just throw around sponsorships like they're nothing.    

Our goal here is to be the best we can be as a whole and having fun while we're 
doing that. Expect a little bit more out of seekers and we come closer to that 
goal. Think about it.

Comments, concerns, flames? Mudmail me.
&amp;r-&amp;WA&amp;wlani&amp;n
save
</text>
