      <text>I also agree. When I look at the seeking list, and I see names after
the person, I expect that person to have had most of his/her questions
answered, and at least the basic knowledge of rp. You don't have to
rp with them until they're masters, obviously, but one session should
be enough to tell you whether or not that person is good to go, or
if he/she needs a bit more work before they're ready to be guilded.
Keep in mind that when you sponsor someone, your name is right there for
all the rest of us to see...if you don't think they're ready, work 
with them a bit more before putting your name there.
Anyway, that's all I have to say about that.
Fayth
